  "local_port": 37024,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to register a startup company for \"Startup India\" campaign and how much will it benefit a startup?",
  "response": "To register a startup company under the \"Startup India\" campaign, you'll need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Incorporate your company**: First, you must incorporate your startup as a private limited company, a partnership firm, or a limited liability partnership (LLP) in India. If your company is already registered, you can directly proceed to the next step.\n\n2. **Visit the Startup India Portal**: Go to the official Startup India website at www.startupindia.gov.in.\n\n3. **Register on the portal**: Click on the \"Register\" button, enter your email ID and mobile number, and verify both using the OTPs sent to you.\n\n4. **Login to the portal**: Once registered, log in using your email ID and password.\n\n5. **Fill the Startup Recognition Form**: After logging in, click on the \"Startup India Services\" tab, and then click on \"Startup Recognition\". Fill out the recognition form with details about your startup, including:\n   - Entity details (company name, registration number, etc.)\n   - Incorporation/Registration Certificate\n   - Details of Directors/Partners\n   - Information about the nature of business\n   - A write-up on the innovative aspect of your business\n\n6. **Upload necessary documents**: You'll need to upload your incorporation/registration certificate and a letter of recommendation from an incubator, angel investor, or any other industry expert.\n\n7. **Submit the form**: After filling out the form and uploading the required documents, submit the form. You will receive an acknowledgement via email.\n\n8. **Wait for recognition**: The Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT) will review your application. If everything is in order, your startup will be recognized as a \"Startup\" under the Startup India initiative.\n\nThe benefits of registering a startup under the Startup India campaign include:\n\n1. **Income Tax Exemption**: Startups can get a tax holiday for 3 consecutive years out of their first 10 years, subject to certain conditions.\n\n2. **Simplified Compliance**: Startups can self-certify compliance with 6 Labour Laws and 3 Environmental Laws.\n\n3. **Easy Winding Up**: In case of exit, startups can wind up operations within 90 days from the date of application for winding up.\n\n4. **Access to Funds**: Startups can apply to the Fund of Funds managed by SIDBI or the Credit Guarantee Scheme.\n\n5. **IPR Fast-Tracking & Rebate**: Startups can fast-track their patent applications and get an 80% rebate on patent filing fees.\n\n6. **Networking Opportunities**: Registered startups gain access to various networking events and workshops organized under the Startup India initiative.\n\nBy registering your startup under the \"Startup India\" campaign, you can take advantage of these benefits and resources to help your business grow and succeed.",
